{
  "doc_id": "12161",
  "text": "In paper [CITATION_1] we considered a dielectric ball placed into high loss liquid at millimeter wave band. So far as the surround liquid has rather small wave resistance, the ball has good resonant characteristics. It is well known that the ball has eigen \"whispering gallery\" oscillations [CITATION_2] . If the outer medium of the ball is high loss liquid, we obtained that the Q-factor of such eigen oscillations in this resonator are of order of several decades and strong depend on complex permittivity of the ball and the surrounded liquid.",
